# Styles and Responsive Design

> **Note**: This file contains redundant rules already covered by `000-senior-developer.mdc`. Consider merging unique content into `111-tailwind-styles.mdc` and removing this file.

## UI and Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS only** for styling (no Shadcn UI, no Radix)
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS using a mobile-first approach
- For Astro, use `astro add tailwind` to configure Tailwind CSS
- Create reusable Astro components with Tailwind
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in components
- Avoid inline styles except for dynamic values
- Use CSS variables for recurring values (colors, spacing)

## Responsive Design

- Use a mobile-first approach with Tailwind
- Test on different screen sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Ensure content is readable and usable on mobile
- Avoid horizontal zoom on mobile (appropriate viewport)
